{
    title: "Insecure Use of `logging.config.listen` Detected",

    summary: "Static code analysis detected the `logging.config.listen` feature was being used in an insecure manner. In some scenarios, untrusted code could be run under the account of the process which calls `listen()`.",

    description: "The `logging.config.listen` function provides the ability to listen for external configuration files on a socket server. Because portions of the configuration are passed through `eval()`, use of this function may open its users to a security risk. While the function only binds to a socket on localhost, and so does not accept connections from remote machines, there are scenarios where untrusted code could be run under the account of the process which calls `listen()`.\n\n{% include '../generic_source_code_issue/description' %}",

    recommendations: "The `logging.config.listen` function provides the ability to verify bytes received across the socket with signature verification or encryption/decryption.",

    details: "{% include '../generic_source_code_issue/details' %}",

    references: [
        "https://docs.python.org/3/library/logging.config.html#logging.config.listen",
    ],
}
